entries.meaning: Any of genus Gonorynchus (also called beaked sandfishes), long, thin ray-finned fishes (family Gonorychidae)

definitionGroups.group: Any of several marine fishes that burrow into sandy seabeds

entries.meaning: in Trichodontidae, a family of perch-like fish
of species Awaous tajasica, usually sand fish, a species of goby fish (family Gobiidae)
of species Malacanthus plumieri (sand tilefish, family Malacanthidae)
of species Diplectrum formosum (sand perch, family Serranidae)

definitionGroups.group: Other animals that notably burrow in sand:

entries.meaning: sandfish skink (Scincus scincus), a land-dwelling lizard that swims in sand
a sea cucumber of species Holothuria scabra or Thelenota ananas.
